# Command Format Enforcement

## Format Rules

Required structure: Title (H1) → Overview (H2, 2-4 sentences) → Steps (H2 with H3 numbered) → Checklist (H2, verifiable items)

**1. Title (H1)**: H1 heading (`#`), Title Case, filename: kebab-case matching title, no version numbers

**2. Overview (H2)**: H2 heading (`##`), 2-4 sentences max, answer "What?" and "When?", no implementation details

**3. Steps (H2)**: H2 heading (`##`), each step: H3 (`###`) with numbered bold title, sequential and actionable, include code/commands where relevant

**4. Checklist (H2)**: H2 heading (`##`), GitHub checkboxes (`- [ ]`), verifiable items, 3-7 items, completion criteria

## Optional Sections
Examples (if complex), Notes (if warnings exist)

## File & Directory Rules

**Naming**: kebab-case, descriptive, action-oriented, match title, `.md` extension

**Placement**: Managing THIS repo? → `.cursor/commands/` (meta-level), else → application directories (`backend-commands/`, `go-backend-commands/`, `user-commands/`, `devops-commands/`)

## Enforcement

**Creating commands**: Use `create-ai-command.md`, validate Title/Overview/Steps/Checklist present, check filename and heading levels

**Common violations**: Missing sections, wrong heading levels, non-actionable checklist items

**After creation**: Update `.cursor/README.md` inventory, use `check-similar-commands.md` to prevent duplicates, test command
